comment:
TRIGGER  WARNING ‚ö†Ô∏è: i talk about about su**ide, self mut***tion, dr*gs and  the sigma surrounding people with BPD and it‚Äôs symptoms so if you don‚Äôt wanna hear about any of that don‚Äôt read on and have a lovely day. 

If not buckle up, this is long but very important.
 
I think what Sia said on her Twitter was very dangerous. If it‚Äôs made up and she doesn‚Äôt have borderline personality disorder, just a dick move. if she does really have borderline personality disorder, why would Sia blare it out there on her huge platform. Sia isn‚Äôt insulting the accused by saying she has it. Having a mental health illness, isn‚Äôt an insult. Sia is insulting the illness itself, the people who have it and she‚Äôs allowing the people who wont look into it to read and assume BPD and abusers go hand in hand. Almost definitely not what she intended but there‚Äôs enough people who certainly did take it as ‚ÄúBPD BAD‚Äù for it to be worrying.

So allow me to explain:

Borderline Personality Disorder (BPD) is an often misunderstood, serious mental health illness, that creates significant emotional instability. Hence why it more recently got its name changed to Emotionally Unstable Personality Disorder (EUPD). Although, a lot of people still use the term BPD when referring to it because it‚Äôs already stuck and it‚Äôs shorter/easier.

4.5 million people in the US experience Borderline personality disorder, that‚Äôs about 1-2% of the population. 

7/10 attempt suicide 
1/10 commit

50-80% partake in drug abuse and self mutilation.

And here‚Äôs just a list of other symptoms:

‚Ä¢feeling fundamentally flawed or worthless
‚Ä¢intensively distorted self image
‚Ä¢extreme fear of abandonment 
‚Ä¢intense rapid mood swings
‚Ä¢impulsive behaviour (to do with ones self such as driving WAY past the speed limit in the pouring rain or something)
‚Ä¢reoccurring suicidal behaviour
‚Ä¢severe dissociative symptoms (loosing touch of reality) 
‚Ä¢self awareness with no out 
‚Ä¢stormy interpersonal relationships (a lot partners come and go)
‚Ä¢anger sometimes explosive in nature

You see those last too and think ‚Äúah scary‚Äù right? That‚Äôs what I imagine but I don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs fair. Just because someone with BPD gets angry doesn‚Äôt mean they are going to hurt anyone. What‚Äôs way more likely, is that they hurt themselves. 

It can be inherited and it can occur after a childhood trauma, manipulations or neglect and can occur for other reasons we don‚Äôt even know about.

And unfortunately it‚Äôs not ‚Äòcurable‚Äô its just something a lot of people just have to live with.

comment:
The truth is still the truth... in that crazy boy toys, do in fact actually drive their significant others coocoo. At some point, a female clues into her reality of infidelity; lies; and narcissism. These are very real truths about being a male whom, does not or cannot settle in or commit to one attentive relationship.
In fact, the heart throb is someone many ppl envy.  But the outcomes of continually being groomed in this manner from a young age. These are the risks to in turn pursue women of the same backgrounds.
Women whom are emotionally charged without moral directive as a youth, easily misinterpret their own beliefs and personal experiences.  The hope in these situations, is that only life in maturity can teach the more average individual. Where men, whom can and do have any women they want.  Can of sorts, 'wake up', and thus appreciate a more stable lifestyle. It is tragic, that women tend to be at higher risk, to re-establish stability. Even than, the actual re-establishinv of psychological restructuring.  Is very intense and thoroughly guaranteed.
Therefore, if any child cannot or does not have proper parenting in place before hand, the cycles of inaccuracy are often much too overwhelming,  to overcome. So, whatever tragedies there are in inheritance, in even generations beforehand. The capacity to changes these or recognize them are very minimal.
As a First Nation Canadian mother, I myself stay hopeful... I advocate from a family level. And I under took the psychological changes that I needed, in order to thrive. I see the adversity firsthand against my children. And my reasoning for not conforming to unhealthy people, is commonly despised. Thankfully, for myself, I grew up with a sense of reasoning compassion and wisdom for right and wrong. Where, I have been able to seemingly avoid direct dysfunctions and keep a clear perspective about truth.
In contrast to this however, I do in fact suffer immensely with isolation effects. I dont have very severe symptoms of doubt. But now that I have matured, I do question my motives of vanity in opposition to family violence. So technically, I have similar struggles to which I do in fact identify.  Where vanity as an onset, does play a role in my capacity to cope. Which, in contrast, my own reasoning for companionship is from the second nature of my family life struggles.
I, commit very devotingly to a healthy and safe home, for my children. Where the only true saving grace, that I can believe in, is in fact the truth.  When people are abusive, and tend to blame and lie, rather than interpretion themselves in the situation.  It just seems more protective and humane, to speak about problems from beginning to end, with healthy outcomes as the benefactor. I feel like, if my children learnwhy it is important to choose the right. Than the possibilities of firgiveness and in meeting good people in the world. Is their best allie. I dont know what the mental health risks are for, the very real levels of disruption that I have been living with, along side unwell family members. 
It actually seems horrifying. And I think this is another area where, even my children knowing the reality of human life at home, in the family. Are better than living at risk. Thinking that ppl and life situations are normal, when they are not.
As our own family unit. We stay hopeful through volunteering and donating food to the essential workers, whom spend a lot of time away from their own homes and families.
We have a little area of loving appreciation from the faces in the community we often see.and its so nice to bting that light in their smiles, when they see us! I am never short of conversations to revelate my belonging.
Perhaps one day, I can at least forgive the anger and unwellness in my own upbringing, that I am unable to allow in my own life.
My parents have been separated since I was 3, I am the product of the end of their first marriages and former families. My father continued on with addictional relationships and children. Where his life long struggle with depression and racism, ended within the dis-unity of his own home, where his health complications were far beyond manageable.
I have always been deeply in love with my dad, and my siblings, to which I find the truth much more soothing to know the reality of the problematic circumstances by which I struggle with. I know God is real, and I do not blame the Father son and the Holy Spirit üíú Thank you.

comment:
I have followed this case for some time now and have seen the court documents and the evidence presented. There is  no doubt in my mind at all that Amber Heard is not only the abuser in this case, but a blatant liar and shameless manipulator.
But no-one should take anyones word for that. Go and review the evidence and the facts of the case available and make up your own mind. 
It's so vitally important in this time of hearsay and media bias and dishonesty, to be able to access facts and evidence so you can determine their credibility for yourself.
The channels that I follow and  know to be covering this case in depth, going over evidence and court documents, are the following: 

Lost Beyond Pluto    (she is a lawyer and goes through the court documents and the case from a law perspective -very informative)
ThatUmbrellaGuy    (Great content, always directly backed by the latest evidence)
Stevie J Raw     (also absolutely excellent at going through the evidence and facts - has full readings of witness and defence statements)
Come Geek Some    (same, references and goes over facts and court documents)
Colonel Kurtz     (has very interesting in-depth content on the case from a more psychological/philosophical angle)

As mentioned, Stevie J Raw has uploaded FULL unedited readings of the court statements of Amber Heard, Johnny Depp and other important key persons in the case, giving you direct access to their own statements so you can compare and come up with your own opinion as to who is telling the truth.

comment:
I have not watched television in over 12 years and do not have it in my home, but prior to that I seldom watched television or was enambered by celebrity.  

Celebrity worship is nothing but fawning over someone that makes more money that anyone really deserves to make and most likely does very little with it to contribute to a better society.  It may even be very difficult ethically for a person of such celebrity to be of an ethical, moral, logical and scientific mind to even see what needs to be addressed in society. Many celebrities go by which way the wind is blowing and what is popular because that also feeds the monster and the monster feeds them.  

Amber Heard is lying by her actions in the interview.  She definitely has a personality disfunction.  Anyone getting involved with a personaity disfunction such as Amber Heards will come out thinking they went through the black hole.  That seems to even be putting it mildly.  That is not just Amber Heard but any personality like hers is a nightmare and confusing to the person at the other end of of the personaities abuse.  

My shock is not this marriage and divorce because it was inevitable but the shock is that Johnny Depp, the wonderful loving companion and father of two children never married the mother of his children after 14 years but instead folded the relationship.

It does not take JD long to marry Heard, though.  So, my question is, did Karma do a full circle to Johnny Depp?  What is his future?

Karma is a dynamic spiritual cycle of actions and effects that we directly control through our thoughts, decisions, and actions. When we create positive choices and thoughts, we will receive positive outcomes. Not because it is fated, but because this is the natural consequence of the previous actions we took.

I hope that Johnny Depp can reconcile his view of what is worthy and precious in relationships  and rectify the failings of not marrying the mother of his children..  What he did to their mother is not respectable except to the tinsil town culture of excesses, sexual deviant trash and over the top excessive materialism.  


He can do better than that!
